cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.HC 

This paper primarily focuses on the social aspects of remixing in a community of young people on a social media sharing website. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer and Society (cs.CY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the ways in which users respond to remixing, which involves social interactions and communication, making the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Social and Behavioral Sciences (cs.SOC) sub-categories also likely. The paper also analyzes the qualities of originators and their projects that correspond to a higher likelihood of plagiarism accusations, which could fall under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) or Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the similarities between a remix and the work it is based on, which could fall under the Signal Processing (cs.SD) sub-category.
